{"word":"H3833 - לָבִיא - lâbîyʼ - law-bee' - Lion","slug":"H3833","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">לָבִיא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lâbîyʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>law-bee'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Lion"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DC;&#x05D1;&#x05D0;&#x05D5;&#x05EA;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05DC;&#x05D1;&#x05D0;&#x05D9;&#x05DD;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05DC;&#x05D1;&#x05D9;&#x05BC;&#x05D0;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05DC;&#x05D1;&#x05D9;&#x05D0; - la&#x0302;b&#x0131;&#x0302;y'  l<sup>e</sup>b&#x0131;&#x0302;ya&#x0302;'  l<sup>e</sup>ba&#x0302;'&#x0131;&#x0302;ym  l<sup>e</sup>ba&#x0302;'o&#x0302;th</b> - <i>law-bee' leb-ee-yaw' leb-aw-eem' (-oth')</i><p/>From an unused root meaning to <i>roar</i>; a <i>lion</i> (properly a <i>lioness</i> as the fiercer (although not a <i>roarer</i>; compare <a href=\"#/H738\">H738</a>)): - (great, old, stout) lion, lioness, young [lion]."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3822\">H3822</a>"}]}